<DOC><DOCNO> AP900601-0094 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-01-90 1241EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-SoccerScreams     06-01 0210</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Soccer Screams,0214</SECOND><HEAD>Rajneesh's Doctor Says Screaming Can Stop Hooliganism</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The doctor of the late free-love guruOsho Rajneesh claimed Friday that he has discovered a cure forsoccer hooliganism: screaming.   Swami Amrito, a British physician, said if soccer fans screamedfor 10 minutes before and after every match, there would be noreason to worry about violence.   ``All that's needed to stop the rising tide of soccer hooliganismaround next month's World Cup match in Italy is that all soccer fansshould have a good catharsis,'' Amrito said, according to a pressrelease issued by the Rajneesh commune in Poona. Amrito said playersshould also participate in the ``screaming meditation.''   ``That will reduce the violence on the field as well as encouragesome poetry and grace in their play,'' he said.   Amrito has been one of the leaders of the Rajneesh commune sincethe guru, who was once known as Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh, died inJanuary.   Rajneesh preached a philosophy of quick-fix enlightenment,telling his followers that only through the indulgence of sensualpleasures could one achieve ``inner peace.''   He was expelled from the United States in 1985 for violatingimmigration laws. At one time his group operated a huge commune inOregon.</TEXT></DOC>